# Project Structure

Verse is a full-stack application with a FastAPI backend and React frontend.

## Directory Structure

- `/apps/backend`: Python FastAPI backend
  - `/app`: Main backend application code
    - `/core`: Core configuration
    - `/crud`: Database CRUD operations
    - `/db`: Database models and connection
    - `/models`: Data models
    - `/routers`: API endpoints
    - `/schemas`: Pydantic schemas
    - `/services`: Business logic and external services
    - `/utils`: Utility functions
  - `/tests`: Backend tests
  - `/alembic`: Database migrations

- `/apps/frontend`: React TypeScript frontend
  - `/src`: Frontend source code
    - `/pages`: Page components
    - `/components`: Reusable UI components
    - `/services`: API clients and services
    - `/utils`: Utility functions
    - `/types`: TypeScript type definitions

Always maintain this structure when adding new files to the project.
